 All the entrances to the caves, which have been dubbed “The Seven Sisters,” are at least 100 to 250 meters in diameter.
 Infrared images reveal, due to the variations in temperature during the day and night, that these are probably caves.
 “They are cooler than the surrounding surface during the day and warmer at night.”
