 If you saw the movie National Treasure, you may think that a treasure map was drawn on the back of the Declaration of Independence.
 However, this is not true. Although there is an inscription on the back of the document, it is not a treasure map.
 On the back of the Declaration of Independence, the words "Original Declaration of Independence dated July 4, 1776" were printed on the back of the document, upside down.
 Although no one knows who actually wrote it, it is known that at an early stage of its existence, the Great Scroll (which measures about 29 and three-quarters inches by 24 inches) was stored rolled up.
 It is therefore likely that the rating was added simply as a label.
