 Ancient China had a unique way of showing the different eras; each stage of China or each family that was in power was a distinct dynasty.
 Between each dynasty, there was also an unstable age of divided provinces. The best known of these periods is the Three Kingdoms era which lasted 60 years between the Han dynasty and the Jin dynasty.
 During these periods, fierce struggles took place between many members of the nobility who fought for the throne.
 The Three Kingdoms was one of the bloodiest periods in the history of ancient China. Thousands of people died in battle to sit on the throne of the great palace of Xi'an.
 There are many social and political repercussions such as the use of the metric system, the shift from absolutism to republicanism, nationalism and the belief that the country belongs to the people and not to one leader.
 Also, after the Revolution, trades were opened to all male candidates, allowing the most ambitious and talented to succeed.
 The same is true for the army, as the ranking of the armies is no longer based on class, but on caliber.
 The French Revolution also inspired many other oppressed working classes in other countries to begin their own revolutions.
 Muhammad was deeply interested in issues that transcended the mundane affairs of this life. He used to frequent a cave which became famous as “Hira’” on the mountain of “Noor” (light) for contemplation.
 The cave itself, which has survived to the present day, gives a very vivid picture of Muhammad’s spiritual leanings.
 Located at the top of one of the mountains north of Mecca, the cave is completely isolated from the rest of the world.
 In reality, it's not easy at all to find, even though we know it exists. When we entered the cave, we were completely isolated.
 Above, one can only contemplate the clear and magnificent sky and the many surrounding mountains. From the inside of the cave, one can see or hear very little of this universe.
 The Great Pyramid of Giza is the only one of the seven wonders that still exists today.
 Built by the Egyptians during the third millennium B.C., the Great Pyramid is one of many giant structures erected in honor of deceased pharaohs.
 The Giza plateau, or "Giza Necropolis", in the Valley of the Kings in Egypt, is home to several pyramids (the Great Pyramid being the largest), several smaller tombs, numerous temples, and the Great Sphinx.
 The Great Pyramid was built to honor Pharaoh Khufu, and many smaller pyramids, tombs, and temples were built to honor his wives and family members.
 The "push" symbol looks like a V and the "pull" symbol looks like a staple or a square with the bottom missing.
 The top means you have to start with the tip and push the bow, and the bottom means you have to start with the nock (which is where your hand holds the bow) and pull the bow.
 An up bow generally produces a softer sound, while a down bow is louder and more assertive.
 Feel free to mark your own marks in pencil, but remember that the printed bow marks are for a musical reason, and should therefore generally be respected.
