 The beaches of the North Shore (in the North Harbour district) are on the Pacific Ocean and stretch from Long Bay in the north to Devonport in the south.
 Almost all beaches are sandy and safe for swimming, and most are shaded by pohutukawa trees.
 The beaches of Tamaki Drive are on the Waitemata Harbour, in the chic suburbs of Mission Bay and St Heliers in central Auckland.
 These beaches, sometimes very crowded by families, have many shops along the coastline. Swimming is safe.
