 The section between Point Marion and Fairmont has the most difficult driving conditions on the Buffalo-Pittsburgh Turnpike, frequently passing through isolated back country terrain.
 If you are not used to driving on country roads, keep your mind open: steep slopes, narrow roads and tight curves are prevalent.
 The posted speed limits are significantly lower than on the previous and following sections – generally 35 to 40 mph (56-64 km/h) – and their strict observance is even more important than before.
 On the other hand, the mobile service is curiously much stronger here than on many other parts of the road, for example the Pennsylvania Wilds.
