 Most monasteries provide stoles to women who arrive without anything, but if you bring your own, and in addition it has bright colors, you will get a smile from the monk or nun at the entrance.
 Just as men must wear pants covering the knees.
 You can also borrow this garment from the stock at the entrance, but as it is not washed after each use, you may not feel comfortable wearing these skirts. A one-size-fits-all for men!
 Majorcan cuisine, like that of similar Mediterranean areas, is based on bread, vegetables and meat (especially pork), and uses olive oil.
 A simple and popular dinner, especially in summer, is Pa amb Oli: bread with olive oil, tomato and all the condiments available, such as cheese, tuna, etc.
 All names, followed by the word Sie, which means you, always begin with a capital letter, even in the middle of a sentence.
 This is a great way to distinguish between certain verbs and objects.
 It can also be said to facilitate reading, although the writing is somewhat complicated by the need to know whether a verb or an adjective is used in a substantivized form.
 Pronunciation is relatively easy in Italian, as most words are pronounced exactly as they are written.
 The main letters to watch out for are c and g, as their pronunciation varies depending on the following vowel.
 Also make sure to pronounce “r” and “rr” in a distinct way: “caro” means “dear,” while “carro” means “cart.”
